<div>
<div>
China's air force showcased a suite of new armaments this week, including <a href="https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/china-displays-new-stealth-fighter-in-race-to-match-u-s/ar-AA1tWb4O">a new stealth fighter and an attack drone</a>, demonstrating its advancing ability to challenge the U.S. military presence in the Asia Pacific. From a report:<i> The public debut of the J-35A stealth fighter and other weapons systems at China's premier airshow, which started Tuesday, represent the centerpiece in the Chinese air force's celebrations of its 75th anniversary -- a milestone in Chinese leader Xi Jinping's sweeping campaign to modernize the People's Liberation Army. <br> <br>
